text: I saw your response last night and got to thinking. I think Wedge makes a good point here. Yes, the government and it's leaders are corrupt, but the individuals in the military who have to carry out orders they don't necessarily agree with do deserve more support than they get. Stuff like care packages are small and not near the amount of help they need(I've heard so many VA horror stories, but again, that's not the soldiers fault) but something like care packages I've been told by a few buddies make a world of difference. I think it's great.
Also, just because you support soldiers doesn't mean you support why they're over wherever they're deployed.
Supporting the military and support LGBT+ rights aren't mutually exclusive either like many people are trying to conjure up
Ah. Did my message yesterday come across as being against supporting troops?
I didn't see it that way, I think you brought up a good point being someone ACTUALLY in the military.
Soldiers don't get much/good help adjusting to life after and it sucks. I think it's worth bringing that up like you did.

Ah alright. Good, I was worried I worded my message last night poorly and gave people the wrong idea. For the record, I'm not against sending care packages to troops. Quite the contrary, they're typically tons of fun / a bright moment in bad situations. I just don't think people understand how very rarely I would ever consider receiving care packages, even from my family sending me things they KNOW I would like / want equates to what I think most troops would want in terms of "mental health care".

I agree that mental health as a bigger picture isn't getting the attention it should, but I don't think that takes away from what they're trying to accomplish here. It's such a bigger thing than WotC can start to get involved with, and this is a nice "we want to help SOMEHOW"
I also have never been and never can imagine the stress of military life, so take everything I say with that grain of salt however big
I agree w/ what you're saying. Also for the record
I probably just came off too negatively about a topic that some people are blatantly attacking Wizards for
Yea, the reaction by the people was really dumb
Thus my thought of "supporting cause X and cause Y are not mutually exclusive" in this case
